{{Infobox Magazine | title = Celtic Family Magazine | image_file = Spring_Issue_of_Celtic_Family_Magazine.png | image_caption = Issue 3 Spring 2014 Artwork designed by Lorin Morgan-Richards. | frequency = Quarterly | language = [[American English]], [[British English]], [[Canadian English]], [[Australian English]] | category = [[Literature]] | publisher = [[Lorin Morgan-Richards]] | firstdate = September 2013 | country = [[United States]] | website = | issn = }}
'''''Celtic Family Magazine''''' was a [[Los Angeles]], California-based print and electronic publication, serving Celtic communities and their descendants around the world.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.isleofman.com/News/details/61744/acclaimed-local-portrait-artist-features-in-us-magazine |title=Acclaimed local portrait artist features in US Magazine |publisher=Isle of Man News |date=2014-02-20 |accessdate=2014-03-18}}</ref> ''Celtic Family Magazine'' published special features and articles on art, history, culture, entertainment, and lifestyle.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.freepressseries.co.uk/news/10702146.Abergavenny_writer__has_role_in_new_magazine/ |title=Abergavenny writer has role in new magazine |publisher=Free Press Series |date=2013-09-26 |accessdate=2014-03-18}}</ref> ''Celtic Family Magazine'' was produced by A Raven Above Press and was distributed throughout North America and select areas of the United Kingdom.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.carmarthenjournal.co.uk/Carmarthenshire-Hollywood/story-20445486-detail/story.html |title=From Carmarthenshire to Hollywood |publisher=Carmarthen Journal |date=2014-01-15 |accessdate=2014-03-18 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140319001217/http://www.carmarthenjournal.co.uk/Carmarthenshire-Hollywood/story-20445486-detail/story.html |archivedate=2014-03-19 |df= }}</ref>
It was announced through social media that after four years of publication Celtic Family Magazine would be going on hiatus starting in 2017.
