The '''Cloëtta Prize''' (Deutsch: ''Cloëtta-Preis''; French: ''Prix Cloëtta'') is a [[Switzerland|Swiss]] distinction to honour personalities who have distinguished themselves in [[biomedical research]].<ref name=official>{{cite web|url=http://www.cloetta-foundation.ch/en/cloetta-prize/|title=Cloëtta Prize|publisher=Cloetta Foundation|accessdate=12 December 2017}}</ref>
Worth 50,000 [[Swiss francs]], it has been awarded annually by the Max Cloëtta Foundation (based in [[Zurich]]), since 1974.<ref name=official/>
