The '''Nasozai'''  ({{lang-ps|نسوزئ}}) are a [[Pashtun people|Pashtun]] tribe.  They are largely literate. Nasozai is the second largest and most important ''[[mohallah]]'' of the village of [[Nartopa]] in [[Attock District]], [[Punjab, Pakistan]], naming that part of the village after their tribe. The people of Nasozai migrated from [[Afghanistan]] (Nasozai) to [[Chhachh]], [[Attock District]] in 1723. {{citation needed|date=October 2017}}

